Two senior Catholic cardinals are set to arrive in the besieged Eastern European nation of Ukraine in the next few days to provide humanitarian support, according to the Vatican. Konrad Krajewski, a 58-year-old Pole, is already on his way to the Ukrainian border with Poland to talk with refugees and helpers. Michael Czerny, a 75-year-old Canadian, is expected in Hungary on Tuesday, where he is expected to also meet with refugees. Afterward, both are set to cross the border into Ukraine proper.   Britain: Visa numbers for fleeing Ukrainians to rise ‘very…     Ukraine: KPMG withdraws operation in Russia, Belarus     Japan to supply Ukraine with steel helmets soon   Czerny has a long interest in migrant rights and is the acting prefect for the Dicastery for Promoting Integral Human Development. Pope Francis announced the trips on Sunday but did not mention Russia at the time. (dpa/NAN)